name: createGuestSession
desc:
This method will let you create a new guest session.
Guest sessions are a type of session that will let a user rate movies and TV shows
but not require them to have a TMDb user account.
More information about user authentication can be found
here.

name: createRequestToken
desc:
Create a temporary request token that can be used to validate
a TMDb user login.
More details about how this works can be found
here

name: createSession
desc:
You can use this method to create a fully valid session ID once a user
has validated the request token.
More information about how this works can be found
here.

name: createSessionFromV4AccessToken
desc:
Use this method to create a v3 session ID if you already have a valid v4 access token.
The v4 token needs to be authenticated by the user.
Your standard "read token" will not validate to create a session ID.

name: createSessionWithLogin
desc: creates a request token with your tmdb user id and password using which you can generate a session

name: deleteSession
desc:
If you would like to delete (or "logout") from a session,
call this method with a valid session ID.

name: getValidationUrl
desc: Returns a validating URL which can be used to create approve request

name: createAccessToken
desc:
This method will finish the user authentication flow and issue an official user access token.
The request token in this request is sent along as part of the POST body.
You should still use your standard API read access token for authenticating this request.

name: createRequestToken
desc:
This method generates a new request token that you can ask a user to approve.
This is the first step in getting permission from a user to read and write data on their behalf.
You can read more about this system here.

name: deleteAccessToken
desc: This method gives your users the ability to log out of a session.

name: getWatchProviders
desc:
Powered by our partnership with JustWatch,
you can query this method to get a list of the
availabilities per country by provider.
This is not going to return full deep links,
but rather, it's just enough information to
display what's available where.
You can link to the provided TMDB URL to help
support TMDB and provide the actual deep links to the content.
Please note: In order to use this data you must attribute
the source of the data as JustWatch. If we find any usage not
complying with these terms we will revoke access to the API.
